<plot>This documentary features commentary by noted historian Thomas D. Clark as he discusses the importance of carrying on tradition and values through the generations with a look at the country store, the weekly newspaper, the small-town post office, and the front porch. The program was illustrated with photographs from James Archambeault, narrated by Bob Edwards of NPR, and scored by Kinny Landrum. Produced, directed, shot and edited by Arthur Rouse of the Media Collaboratory</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?199659</url></doc>
